30
00:02:45.640 --> 00:02:49.450
and path selection between two host systems

31
00:02:49.570 --> 00:02:57.100
that may be located on geographically separated networks. The Network Layer is the layer that manages

32
00:02:57.100 --> 00:03:05.920
the connectivity of hosts by providing logical addressing. IP addressing is our logical addressing.

33
00:03:05.920 --> 00:03:09.450
Next layer is Layer 2, the Data Link Layer.

34
00:03:09.520 --> 00:03:15.930
The most important information here is the source and destination Layer 2 address.

35
00:03:16.000 --> 00:03:23.260
Again, just like with Layer 3 and 4, there is other information also included in the Layer 2 header.

36
00:03:23.260 --> 00:03:30.130
